verbose_text: However, following exposure to ROS, Nrf2 dissociates from cytosolic Keap1 and translocates to the nucleus, where it binds to the antioxidant response element (ARE) in the promoter regions of the genes that encode antioxidant enzymes and induce their transcription.
evidence: Nrf2 dissociates from cytosolic Keap1 and translocates to the nucleus
